commit.message:
Let `isdisjoint` return `True` when the sets are disjoint

Fix bug where `isdisjoint` only returned `False` for non-disjoint set,
never `True` for actually disjoint sets.

commit.message: update tests & docs for up to Python 3.6

README - add syntax highlighting

It's a little easier to read.

Include tests in sdist

The tests are desirable to have in the source distribution for Linux packaging purposes. After merging this change, please consider making a new release on PyPI which will now include the tests. Thanks.

Merge pull request #9 from simonpercivall/feature/unordered-comparisons

Make comparisons against all sets unordered.

Make comparisons against all sets unordered.

This is a breaking change. Comparisons against other OrderedSets are now
performed unordered, except for equality checks.

Two new methods have been added to perform ordered comparisons.
Fix tests for Python 2.6.
Add Python 3.5 to test targets.

Make OrderedSet handle being on the right-hand side of a set operation.

The set operations lacked implementation to handle the "self" parameter
not being itself, as Cython reverses the arguments instead of having
__r*__ methods.

Fix a "related" bug with intersection using the right-hand argument for
order.
Remove Cython as docs dependency from tox.ini, it's in test_requirements.
Stop using the Sphinx changelog extension.
